# Final Assessment Project Pitch  
## Working Title: **Living Score**

---

## Part 1: Project Direction

Our team has chosen to create an **original interactive audiovisual piece**.

### Team Vision

Our project, **Living Score**, is an original interactive audiovisual artwork where visuals and music influence each other. Instead of making a simple music visualiser where shapes only react to sound, we want to create a system where the artwork can also shape the music. The project will use a WAV audio track together with MIDI data to create musical outputs such as drum hits, piano notes, guitar notes, and bass notes. These outputs will trigger visual changes, while some visual elements may also control the music by muting, unmuting, switching, or changing the volume of different musical parts.

The inspiration comes from generative music visual projects such as Patt Vira’s *Rainbow Pendulum Waves* and *Musical Onion*, where movement, rhythm, colour, and note values are connected through code. We are also inspired by abstract audio visualisers that use circles, waves, pulses, and particles to represent musical energy. Our aim is to create a living audiovisual system where music, visuals, timing, randomness, and user control feel connected.

